# Cursor Rules — Golf Physics Field Guide

## Project Overview
Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + KaTeX + Recharts
A magazine-quality physics reference for wedge ball-striking mechanics.

## Architecture
- All page content lives in `src/app/page.tsx`
- Physics data (equations, tables) is in `src/lib/physics-data.ts`
- Reusable components in `src/components/`

## Design System
- Paper background: `#f5f0e8` (cream)
- Accent (crimson): `#8b1a1a`
- Gold: `#b8860b`
- Ink (text): `#1a1410`
- Use CSS variables from `globals.css` or Tailwind tokens from `tailwind.config.ts`

## Equations
- All display math uses `<BlockMath>` from `react-katex`
- All inline math uses `<InlineMath>` from `react-katex`
- Wrap in `<EquationBlock>` component for styled equation boxes
- LaTeX strings use double backslash: `\\frac{1}{R}` not `\frac{1}{R}`

## Charts
- Use Recharts for all data visualizations
- Charts must be `'use client'` components
- Wrap with `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })` in page.tsx

## Tables
- Use the `<DataTable>` component — never raw HTML tables in page.tsx
- Add data to `physics-data.ts`, consume in page.tsx
- `tourKey` prop highlights the tour-standard row in crimson

## Typography
- Headings: `var(--font-playfair)` — Playfair Display
- Body: `var(--font-source-serif)` — Source Serif 4
- Code/numbers: `var(--font-jetbrains)` — JetBrains Mono

## Adding Content
1. New equation → add to `EQUATIONS` array in `physics-data.ts`
2. New table data → add typed constant in `physics-data.ts`
3. New chapter → add section in `page.tsx`, add to `CHAPTERS` in `physics-data.ts`
4. New chart → create component in `components/`, import with `dynamic()` in page

## Code Style
- Functional components only
- No class components
- `'use client'` only when needed (charts, Sidebar)
- Prefer named exports for components
